            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                <head>No. 109.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Tenterden</persName> to Earl <persName type="to">Granville</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 14, 1872</date>.
                                (Received June 21.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[From British Blue Book “North America,” No. 10, (1872,) p.
                            2.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to report that I
                            arrived here this morning, in company with the Lord Chief Justice, Sir
                            R. Palmer, Mr. Sanderson, Mr. Lee Hamilton, and Mr. Langley.</p>
                <p>Count Sclopis, Baron Itajuba, Mr. Adams, and Mr. Bancroft Davis, together
                            with the United States Counsel, Mr. Evarts, Mr. Cushing, and Mr. Waite,
                            are here, and M. Staempfli is expected to arrive this evening or
                            to-morrow morning.</p>
                <p>The meeting of the Tribunal has been fixed for 12 o’clock to-morrow, the
                            15th instant, in pursuance of the resolution adopted on the 15th of
                            December last.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>TENTERDEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
